I pause when understanding finally manifests. It is a world that works
the way you think it ought to work. That's _exceedingly_ convenient.

Hailing is done, not by some identification scheme and magical radio, but
by giving the hailer a clear enough picture of the vessel hailed. The color
codes are not unique, but merely serve to help specify.

The simplest, bluntest method is to use a pentagram, draw up the color code and
identifying characteristics, and write the intended message, both in porting
ink. Almost all ships will have receivers set up to receive such messages.


